headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns wasn't shooting for a trophy or title. This time, his clutch 3-pointer saved the Timberwolves.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns hits late 3-pointer as T-Wolves hold off Cavs 127-122

headlines.description: — Wendell Carter Jr. had 21 points and 12 rebounds, Markelle Fultz scored 10 points in his return from injury and eight Orlando players scored in double figures as the Magic beat the Indiana Pacers 119-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fultz scores 10 in return, helps Magic beat Pacers 119-103

headlines.description: — No Kevin Durant, no Steve Nash and nobody who could guard Scottie Barnes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes makes first 11 shots, Raptors romp 133-97 in Brooklyn

headlines.description: — For the first time all season, the Miami Heat have a bit of a cushion atop the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vincent scores 20, Heat remain hot by topping Bulls 112-99

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant threw down a massive dunk over 7-footer Jakob Poeltl and scored a career-high 52 points, lifting the Memphis Grizzlies over the San Antonio Spurs 118-105 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant dunks over 7-footer, scores 52 as Grizzlies top Spurs

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points and 16 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks scored a season-high 44 points in the second quarter on the way to a 130-106 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks score 44 in 2nd quarter, roll past Hornets 130-106

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — DeAaron Fox had 29 points and 10 assists, and the Sacramento Kings rolled past the Oklahoma City Thunder 131-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox's 29 points, 10 assists lead Kings past Thunder, 131-110
